Young Lucretia and Other Stories is a collection of thirteen short stories by Mary Wilkins Freeman, a protégée of William Dean Howells. She is known for having written collections such as A New England Nun and Other Stories and A Humble Romance and Other Stories. The stories in Young Lucretia and Other Stories were originally published in leading literary magazines such as Harper's Young People and St. Nicholas Magazine between 1887 and 1892. They were later collected and reprinted by Harper & Brothers in 1892. These stories primarily feature children who learn moral lessons after misbehaving.